abstract: The modest stock losses came after the S.&.P 500 index gained 6.6 percent in December and 13 percent for the year.

lead_paragraph: Stocks declined on Thursday despite reports showing a drop in jobless claims, the fastest business expansion in two decades and a gain in pending home sales.

headline.print_headline: STOCKS & BONDS; Shares Slip Back From 2-Year Highs
